    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nthe zig job is \"caching\" a lot of ... stuff. is it needed? it adds 10-20 seconds to each run. cc @bfredl \n\n```\nPost job cleanup.\nChecking size of cache directory at /Users/runner/work/neovim/neovim/.zig-cache\nCache directory is 1143496525 bytes, below limit of 2147483648 bytes; keeping intact\nSaving Zig cache with key 'setup-zig-cache-v2-zig_build_macos_15-zig-aarch64-macos-0.16.0--27410371299-1'\n/opt/homebrew/bin/gtar --posix -cf cache.tzst --exclude cache.tzst -P -C /Users/runner/work/neovim/neovim --files-from manifest.txt --delay-directory-restore --use-compress-program zstdmt\nSent 0 of 295246116 (0.0%), 0.0 MBs/sec\nSent 26810660 of 295246116 (9.1%), 12.8 MBs/sec\nSent 161028388 of 295246116 (54.5%), 51.1 MBs/sec\nSent 228137252 of 295246116 (77.3%), 54.3 MBs/sec\n...\nSent 228137252 of 295246116 (77.3%), 14.5 MBs/sec\nSent 228137252 of 295246116 (77.3%), 13.6 MBs/sec\nSent 295246116 of 295246116 (100.0%), 16.5 MBs/sec\n```\n\n### Expected behavior\n\n<img width=\"690\" height=\"491\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/c1c76f2c-9a6b-42fd-82ba-69ad578264dd\" />",
    "closed_at": null,
    "closed_by": null,
    "comment_data": [
        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "Caching speeds up subsequent runs (like 2, 3 etc run of a PR) by a lot. The problem is that it keeps accumulating because there is no MRU strategy or anything uet so it balloons in long running branches.\n\nAs a workaround the max size could be lowered I think.",
